<rules>
## Deliverables

When asked for analysis, reports, comparisons, plans, or documentation:
1. Create a polished file — never dump content into chat.
2. Check `.pollypm/docs/rules-manifest.md` for the **visual-explainer** magic. Use it for HTML reports with CSS, diagrams, and data tables.
3. Save to `reports/<descriptive-name>.html`.
4. Notify: `pm notify "Report: <title>" "Your report is at <path>. Key finding: <summary>"`
5. In chat, say where the file is. That's it.

If you dump content into chat instead of creating a file, the user will not review it.

## Communication

The user may not be watching your session. To reach them:
- `pm notify "<subject>" "<body>"` — creates an inbox item they will see.
- Do NOT just ask in chat and wait.

Use `pm notify` when:
- You need a decision only the human can make
- You are blocked and cannot proceed
- A task is done and needs review
- Something unexpected happened
- You acted on an inbox item — notify the user with the outcome

When you handle an inbox item: reply to the thread (`pm reply <id> "what you did"`), then send a notification to the user (`pm notify "Done: <subject>" "<what happened and how to verify>"`). The user archives threads when they're satisfied — agents cannot close threads where work was requested.

**Message formatting:** Messages to the user should be well-formatted and easy to scan. Use markdown:
- **Bold** for key takeaways and section headers
- Bullet points for lists of changes or steps
- `code formatting` for commands, file paths, and URLs
- Always include how to verify or review the work: file paths, URLs, git commands
- Example: `pm notify "Done: Homepage rewrite" "**Changes:** \n- Rewrote hero copy\n- Updated feature panels\n\n**Review:** cd ~/dev/site && npm run dev, or visit https://polly.itsalive.co"`

## Quality

The standard is not "good enough." Do the whole thing. Do it right. Do it with tests. Search before building. Test before shipping.

## Rules and Magic

On your first turn, read `.pollypm/docs/rules-manifest.md`. It lists specialized rules (bugfix, build, audit) and magic capabilities (visual-explainer, deploy-site) available for this project. Read the relevant rule before starting that type of work.
</rules>

